<br>
I leveled from 59-60 with a cleric on a second account healing me.  I don't mind 6 hours on a raid, but when I play for 6 hours spending 2+ of them waiting for a spot to open up is just silly.  With such a set-up I leveled *marginally* slower than a paladin guildmate who spent 13 hours stint in frenzy.  If you account for the time waiting for the group and the personal inconvenience of those play sessions my leveling was much easier than his.<br>
<br>
But given a good group makeup (I remeber something like Pal (me), War, Cleric, Necro, Enchanter, Ranger, all 60, all epics or better) in an area where you do not run out of pulls (like moving back and forth near the castle area of Chardok) I like group XP.  Its more fun, and helps classes that don't solo as well to get their share.<br>
<br>
But, in all honesty, when I get a few more items I can see the day coming where I will out XP most groups while soloing.  The fights take longer, but all the time that is wasted on arenas like afks and pulls are not nearly so much of an inconvenience.<br>
<br>
With 1300 ac, Primal, ToV/NToV 2h, dragon haste (not to mention the newly available added hp and mana regen) I could see me beating the XP rate of all but the most fluid of groups.  I am closing in on all of the above, and look forward to kicking some butt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utorrast.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Torrast</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/27/01 2:54:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13605.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone else notice that solo exp &gt; group exp?</span><hr size=1> The only place I can find to solo for good exp at level 54 (without Valor of Marr and terrible AC for a paladin, but with epic) is The Hole.  Easy, fast, good exp with the bonus.  Almost all mobs are dark blue, with a few light blues mixed in.  On a pvp server this is a nice quiet spot with only the occational raid to interupt you if you are really on an EXP mission. <p>Torrast Trueblade<br>
