People think that the group exp bonus is extra then what you would get solo.  If you add another person you have an instant 50% exp penalty.  So verant adds a few % for each person, big deal.  With 6 people, you need  to kill 5 times the mobs to equal one mob solo.  This might be poss. in places with endless mobs like DL/OT, but in most places, you are waiting for repops=crap exp.  Solo is the best exp, but groups help break up the grind feeling that soloing creates.  <br>
<br>
I always laugh when someone wants another person for the group for the exp bonus.  Unless you are gonna be able to kill much faster, it will slow exp down with every person you add.  People take more exp then the rotten little token exp bonus you get for adding them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukropotkinnobleblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kropotkin Nobleblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/27/01 8:57:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13605.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://w3.one.net/~hodosko/images/ForwardKnightMarbleBkgd.jpg height=119 width=75></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone else notice that solo exp &gt; group exp?</span><hr size=1> I just hit 59 and have really started soloing for the first time.  I can't believe how the xp is rolling in.   With CC and fighting on a horse so that I can med I have absolutely no downtime.<br>
