<br>
The best experience per hr in the game imo is with a good partner.  I've partnered with about every class and although some are better than others exp is always better than group and solo.  I think best class is actually another pally.  With both helm healing down-time is kept to a minimum.  Cleric seems to be least efficient.  You just can't pull enough to keep a cleric busy.  But I've enjoyed time with wizzy, warrior, rogue, mage, ranger, etc.  <br>
<br>
It is best to partner with a friend as most kids can't tolerate the helm healing.  However as we pallys know while helm healing is slow overall exp is MUCH better than with full group.  And with a partner you're less likely to go insane as soloing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadariansilverthorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adarian Silverthorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/27/01 10:13:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13605.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone else notice that solo exp &gt; group exp?</span><hr size=1> Take this setting and this is why you get better solo exp.<br>
<br>
Solo: Area where you can solo pull and kill the mobs without adds and at least 80% are regular low blue and the rest are light blue. If you have anywhere near a good weapon/haste with VoM you will be dishing out at least 2k per minute. Average best exp mob has around 5k. So it takes you roughly 3 minutes or less to kill it and you spend 1-2 minutes medding/healing and you are back and ready to go. With this setup you can kill roughly 12+ mobs per hour.<br>
<br>
Group: To equal 12 mobs killed solo you will have to kill about 60 mobs in a full group per hour. That means a mob better fall every single minute of the group or you will get less exp. You may do that for the first 10 or so kills but after that it will begin to stretch into 1.2/1.4/1.6 minutes per kill just based on how long it takes the puller to get it back to you. Think of velks and add up every single spider on the ramps. There prolly isn't even 60 total and the pop time is 30 minutes so unless your group is doing 80% of the spiders on the ramps you will not be getting better xp then solo. How many times has your group been told by the puller &quot;Nothin up&quot;.<br>
<br>
Gear/abilities: This changes the effectiveness of soloing so much it is unreal. A Paladin with a 50+damage 40ish delay two hander or a paladin with a 24/22 one hander and with avatar can solo all day long and hardly even slow down. Same goes for very High ac. If your base ac unbuffed is 1250+ then you can tank blue con mobs with just daring up and you might not even have to cc yourself before you kill it. Some alt abilities will also effect how your solo exp comes in. If you went with 3 levels of crits then 3 levels of slay undead and stayed mostly soloing undead you would be able to increase your exp speed. Same thing with taking double reposte or the skill that increases your healing or mana/hp regen or even the one that increases mitigation or evasion. <br>
<br>
Only situation I think you could get better exp then solo is duo with either a Shaman or a Druid. Preferable the Shaman. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uradiation911.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Radiation911</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/27/01 10:32:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13605.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.blizzard.com/images/war3/units/dreadlord.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone else notice that solo exp &gt; group exp?</span><hr size=1> Partner up with a bard, not funny how good this combo is. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3088>Radiation Contamination</a><BR>
